<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by SleepyBhr on 06-11-2002 01:48 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Bennan, you asked for thoughts...

In some cases, it could be an ok idea.  You picked a stupid name you'd regretted for months, and now you have the chance to change it.  It's like the cosmetic surgery you've alwasy wanted.  Then again, for the Iamsnot and Melikepanties characters out there, VI should have been considering changing their names anway.  But, what do you expect from a company who's filtering software doesn't let you hear someone saying "Incoming: a stongazer cockatrice" because cockatrice is a potential "bad word?"

Over all, I don't like it.   A great many things change about your character as you play: clothing, weapons, even your face.  Your name is the only thing that sets you apart from everyone els ein this game -- at least appearance-wise, since everyone plays differently.  As many have mentioned, your name holds your reputation, for good or ill.  I don't want to have to look people up on a web site to see who they are in-game.  That's just too bogus.

The ad iteslef for the service is annoying, too.  It's all sugary and sweet.  It's the Stranger with Candy voice ment to entice you to mindlessly buy their product.  I felt disgust while reading it.

If VI really wanted to help players customize their characters, they would make it easier (ie possible in most cases) to change your surname.  It seems to me that your surname was supposed to be the part of you you can customize to show how your grown as a character.  

I, for one, haven't taken a surname because I dont' feel I have anything too unique to label about myself.  I would definatly if I grandmastered a tradeskill, did or liked something special in the game, or -- pipe dream time -- was allowed to choose some special alternate skill/whatever that would further define my character.  (I've always thought allow a character to pick up one or two alternate skills would be cool.  Not like AA stuff, but something like being able to train in on skill you couldn't in, like foraging or poison or bash, or raise the cap on one skill you had, like swimming or dodge.  And make it available at level 20, when you are able to pick a surname.  I'd pick swimming... but I digress.)

Sanctu
Master Swimmer (200)
39 High Elven Cleric of Tunare
Seventh Hammer Server</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
